ack <shrugs>. I figured I needed 2k and started to save more. A few more days go by and another druid gave me a tell asking how much was I paying I said just tell me what you want he said "How much you paying" I never returned his tell I'm already playing a game didnt wan't to play another. Shouted for almost another week<BR>with no Luck. I headed to GD for another shot with some guildmates but the guardians were camped. Got a tell form a rouge,Druid and Pally asking if we wanted to go to TT I said sure since wurms were camped and I have never been there. There was a lev 52 Cleric shouting wtb Cel Heal paying 1.2k and I said in group I would love to get that spell been trying for weeks. The druid said he had a copy how much was I paying ( at this point I would have paid 2k but told him 1.5k) he said Ok its in bank lets go get. yaahoo finally I was happy to pay the 1.5k. We ended up in TT an I Love this spell btw so does the druid since he was the puller(only one with tracking) and it saved his butt many times. Took me til lev 47 to get but finally I have it Love when the ouller calls INC and ya just slap it on the main tank  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Falconquick<BR>47th Season</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tvenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I read so many horror stories I decided to just buy it.  I went to FP and shouted.  Got a tell from a guy who had it.  I offered 1k and he accepted.  Now I just have to get to 2 more levels so I can use it =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I did the Wurm camps several times with Islington and saw about 4 or 5 copies of the spell drop.  I personally gave 2 away to guildmates.  However hindsight being 20/20, I got screwed in the end.  The copies I saw drop were in the first two weeks of Velious going live when each Guardian was pretty much guaranteed to drop up to three spells.  I went back to the Wurm camp after the infamous “spell drop nerf” and got so frustrated that I vowed to never do it again. Also it just so happens that shortly after I gave the copies away to guildmates, I did so to better the guild and help us out.  Well in both cases the guildmates left the guild shortly after looking for “raiding” style guilds…<P>As soon as Quistil hit 39 I sold off a lot of junk (including my coveted Ghoulbane…  Sigh…) and managed to raise 2.5k (said Ghoulbane just isn’t worth what it once was).  I started to auction in every single zone I was in for Celestial Healing and never got a single tell for a week.  Kept checking with my guild but no joy there either.  I posted on the trades section of my servers board and finally found a seller.  I was hoping to pay 1k or less for the spell.  I was willing to blow the whole 2.5k on it.  He wanted 2k for it but I managed to talk him down to 1.5k.  So I got it for far less than I was willing to buy it for but more than I wanted to.<P>Overall I’m happy though.  It sits in my backpack with my other 44 spells just waiting for the day I can scribe it  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR><P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 40 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nalance</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">< is level 54 and still doesn't have the spell.  I do just fine without it, although I would love to get it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Larkius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ack this isn't sounding too promising!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.