al elixir....at least you can buy that from a vendor.<P>Aladain<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Larkius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well in the off chance I get 2 copies in my travels, I'll make sure to send ya a tell Aladain.  A gift for all your help!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Marvill</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Whenever a post about Cel Heal comes up, people always mention Velk's Lab...  But unless you're in a raiding guild and in your high 50's, Velk's isn't a reality.  So just start auctioning WTB Celestial Healing as soon as you hit 39/40  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  I made a hotkey for it, and got super lucky...  The second time I ever hit the hotkey, I got a tell from a level 60 enchanter in one of our server's uber-guilds asking how much I was offerring, and 1k later I had it in my hands  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  It helps to auction in odd zones though.  For instance, the enchanter saw my auction while she was on a monk epic raid in LOIO.  Don't auction in someplace like Dreadlands, where there are probably four or five other clerics also looking for it.<P>And as for the spell drops--I heard Turning of the Unnatural was upped.  At least, I know it used to go for 1k on The Tribunal, but now it's only 300 (which is what I paid when I bought my copy last night.  I'm such a spell freak, I have every spell 1-44  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">.)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Larkius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah I definatley am determined to have this spell before lvl 44.  But I don't think I've ever had anything over 800pp in the bank.  Well I take that back, had over 1k