 as soon as possible so that we can have it ready when we hit 44.  The section of spell drops in Dexter's Lab is 50+ and the level 40 to 44 Cleric won't be able to get it.<P>I guess the good thing is that it DOES drop here though as it allows Clerics the chance to buy it from the higher levels.  Or those higher levels can pass it down.<P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 41 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Larkius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, same concept as bronze armor that drops in the dreadlands.  No one hunting has a use for it at all other than to give to twinks or lower lvl characters.  <P>Another funny note on my camp for this spell, earlier today a guildie told me he found it off a merchant for around 200pp turns out it was celestial cleansing, the high lvl pally spell hehe I was very excited till I found out what it actually was.  Eh well, maybe tonight is my lucky night.  <BR>Also have a bard who swears he's gonna get it for me since I gave him the coin of the ancients that drops in kaesora.  Heh! Had no idea what it was for but saw him trying to buy it in EC.  He said it was worth 1kpp but I only took 100pp.  Told him that if he did get Celestial heal for me then he gets his 100pp back  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sullah</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Level 53 Here and my group fatality rate remains quite low without this spell.  I think I will try to buy it this weekend though.  Couldn't hurt.   <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aanar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Ari